On 8 August 2010, the Macau Sport Development Board will organize a series 
of activities to propagate the National Fitness Day which endorses its 
commitment to the promotion of Sport for All movement:
1. Facilities of the Macau Sport Development Board and the Civic and 
Municipal Affairs Bureau will be opened for free for the public to take part in 
sport practice. 
2 .From 7am to 11am, "Sport-Health Advisory Station" will be organized at 
"Areia Preta Triangular" Garden to provide physique test for the public.  At the 
same time, advisory information like health analysis, sports scheme and 
nutrition will be provided, giving the citizens a good chance to understand 
their health conditions and to set up an appropriate plan in sport 
participation. In addition, sport demonstration session of the students from 
Recreational & Physical Exercise Classes will be arranged which allows the 
public to experience different kinds of sports and the benefits derived.
3. From 4pm to 7pm, "Sport for All Day" will be organized at the Garden of 
Flower City. With the demonstration of the students from Recreational & 
Physical Exercise Classes and fun activities, citizens will be encouraged to 
participate in sports exercise which enhances the public understanding  the 
importance of sports as well as encouraging them to nurture sport participation 
as a good habit. 